The paper deals with the trade-off between secret message and secret key rates over a wiretap channel with non-causal channel state information, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also focuses on semantic security, which is a concept in cryptography (cs.CR). The use of superposition coding and soft-covering lemma suggests that the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper may have applications in multimedia security (cs.MM) due to its focus on secure communication of secret messages.
